Article.ArticleTitle: Zeaamine, a new amine from roots of Zea mays and its cytotoxic activity against CT26 and SW480 cell lines.

AbstractText: A new amine, zeaamine (1), along with nine known compounds (2-10), were isolated from the roots of Zea mays. Among these, compound 2 was first isolated from this plant, and compound 3 was first isolated from the roots. In the current investigation, the cytotoxicity against CT26 and SW480 cells of the compounds were evaluated. Zeaamine (1) exhibited moderately affected CT26 and SW480 cells with IC50 values of 17.91 and 10.21 µM.
